# MosBot Workspace Service — Rules Overview

These rules exist to keep changes **secure**, **testable**, and **consistent** for a service that can modify files on a mounted workspace volume.

## How and when to use these rules

- `overview.mdc` is **always applied** as the default guidance.
- All other rules are **not always-on** (`alwaysApply: false`). Use them when they match the area you are changing.
- Prefer applying the most relevant rule(s) rather than trying to follow every rule at once.

## Rules index

| File | Covers |
| ---- | ------ |
| `security.mdc` | Secrets, auth defaults, logging hygiene, path safety, Docker/CI considerations |
| `architecture.mdc` | App structure, route conventions, response semantics, error handling, backward compatibility |
| `openclaw-integration.mdc` | Symlink remapping behavior, path normalization, cross-container workspace assumptions |
| `contributing.mdc` | Formatting, tests/coverage gates, dependency hygiene, PR conventions |
